Simon Thomas says nine-year-old son Ethan’s memories of mum are ‘fading’ following her sudden death in November: ‘It's hard to hear’

SIMON Thomas has opened up about the loss of his wife, and how his son is coping with her death.

ok
  • Bookmark
  • Share
TV
By
Nicole DouglasSenior Online Showbiz Reporter
  • 11:35, 20 MAR 2019
  • Bookmark
    • Video Loading

    Join us on WhatsApp

    Former Sky Sports presenter Simon Thomas has opened up about the loss of his wife, and how his son is coping with her death. 

    Gemma, 45, tragically died in November 2017 – just three days after she was diagnosed with acute myeloid leukaemia.

    Speaking on Wednesday's episode of This Morning, Simon – who was married to Gemma for 12 years – opened up about his heartache over nine-year-old son Ethan, admitting he fears his son's memories of his mother are "starting to fade".

    "It’s interesting… because Ethan has a different understanding of death, he absolutely knows that mum is not coming back," the 46 year old told Holly Willoughby and Phillip Schofield.

    “What’s been really difficult for me in the last week is beginning to understand and realise that his memories of the every day with mum are starting to fade. 

    “We were just getting dressed on the landing the other morning, as I’d always do. I was lucky enough to be at home with him most mornings because of my work.

    "I’d get him dressed, mum would be getting dressed, she’d do the school run – and I was doing it with him again the other morning, and he just turned to me and said: ‘Daddy, did you always used to get me dressed in the morning?’

    “I said yes. He said ‘when mummy was alive, did she used to take me to school?’ I said yes, or sometimes I’d do it. Already, nearly 16 months later, his memories of day-to-day life with mum are fading, and that is so hard to hear."

    Revealing how he plans to cherish those memories with his son, he added: "I have got videos, pictures, and memories – that I really need to write down." 

    Simon recently revealed that he’s in the early stages of a new relationship following the devastating loss of his other half.

    It was reported by The Sun that the woman Simon is dating is Derrina Jebb, 27, whom he met through his church, after the publication obtained pictures of the pair grabbing coffee together. 

    Simon previously revealed that, while it felt "strange" to be in a relationship again, he could never replace his late wife.

    Speaking on BBC Radio 5 Live, the presenter said: "Right from the early stages – she had this empathy towards me. She’s Christian as well and that’s important to me as a man of faith.

    "She’s been an incredible support for me. She was the only person who would always pick up the phone.

    "What I saw in her, I saw in Gemma. When she said my phone is always on, she meant it."

    “Sometimes I struggle with the phrase ‘moving on’ – I don’t think you ever really do move on from what’s happened," he continued.

    "That hole that a loved one leaves doesn’t shrink over time. Life begins to grow around it. You begin to deal with some of the challenges grief throws up, being a single parent throws up.

    "I don’t want to [give up]. I’ve got a boy to bring up, I promised Gemma."
